    """
    A structure containing a weak reference to a :class:`GObject.Object`.

    A :class:`GObject.WeakRef` can either be empty (i.e. point to ``None``), or point to an
    object for as long as at least one "strong" reference to that object
    exists. Before the object's :class:`GObject.ObjectClass`.dispose method is called,
    every :class:`GObject.WeakRef` associated with becomes empty (i.e. points to ``None``).

