    references to the object being held (‘re-referencing’), any :class:`GWeakRefs` taken
    before it was disposed will continue to point to ``None``.  Any :class:`GWeakRefs` taken
    during disposal and after re-referencing, or after disposal has returned due
    to the re-referencing, will continue to point to the object until its refcount
    goes back to zero, at which point they too will be invalidated.

    It is invalid to take a :class:`GObject.WeakRef` on an object during :class:`GObject.ObjectClass`.dispose
    without first having or creating a strong reference to the object.
    """
